comment_data.body: Actually, it's alright to keep the `static_link` qualname in this form because it's [only used](https://github.com/cython/cython/pull/6681/files#diff-4eba19c4520bf951ffdae34e4e388821472d0a97e92f430ce61186d6231cfe21R268) if the attribute is [in dir](https://github.com/cython/cython/pull/6681/files#diff-4eba19c4520bf951ffdae34e4e388821472d0a97e92f430ce61186d6231cfe21R264), meaning it will only be called in versions where it's supported.

for backwards compatibility with GDB 12

* Remove code for Python 2 and Python < 3.8.
* Integrate better with Python 3.
* Improve support for the Limited API.
* Start supporting GIL-free Python 3.13.
* Support the Py3.13 `sys.monitoring` API.
* Support and use `am_send` for coroutines.
